Singer Tiwatope Savage aka Tiwa Savage has revealed the man behind her hit track song ‘Somebody’s son’. The award-winning songstress made this known during her performance at the BudXLagos FIFA Kick-Off Concert at Eko Hotel, Lagos over the weekend. While performing, she paused to tell her fans the story behind the hit song.   Tension over alleged murder of woman in Anambra community     England beat Germany to win women Euro 2022     BBNaija Level Up: 26th housemate joins level two housemates   According to her: “I am going to tell you guys this story, when I did this song, yeah, a lot of people were like ‘this is a sure hit but only girls are going to sing this song, guys are not going to sing it. And they were like Tiwa you are taking a risk by making it your first single.’ ”I said to them don’t worry one day I am going to tell this story. You see somebody’s son I was talking about is actually Jesus Christ. For real, so whether you’re a man or woman we are all looking for that somebody’s son right”. Tiwa, who just returned from her 14- week world tour performed alongside Davido, Asake, Reekado Banks, Teni, Mayorkun, and a host of others at the Budweiser concert. The concert is a celebration of the biggest Football platform in the world, the FIFA World Cup Tournament, holding in Qatar.